In 1905, Alberta and Saskatchewan are created as provinces with the boundaries they have today and the District of Keewatin is transferred back to the Northwest Territories.
In 1898, the District of Yukon is separated from the Northwest Territories to become Yukon Territory; its boundaries are changed to those of today in 1901.
The boundaries of Manitoba, Ontario and Quebec are extended northward in 1912 to their present boundaries.
