Mutton and lamb dominate Algerian consumption, closely followed by beef.
Veal, horse and rabbit are also eaten, but in small quantities.
Pork is not marketed in Algeria as it is prohibited by Islam.
Algerian’s are also extensive milk consumers, their needs are estimated at 3 billion liters a year, two thirds of which is imported.
