1.1 Cost of production As the Canadian Apple industry is a major component of the horticulture industry, many producers are afflicted with low returns on investment, even below their costs of production.
Producers claim to loose 22.85 cents per kg (9.25 cents per pound) on average, surviving mostly on depreciation and equity of their assets.
Replant costs are estimated $30,000 to $37,000 per hectare ($12,000 to $15,000 per acre) and full production capacity is not reached until 4 to 6 years following replant.
There is also support from Farm Credit Canada with their program "Plant Now - Pay Later" allowing up to three years of interest deferral.
1.2 Storage Holdings & Utilization With respect to the 2002 crop, total storage holdings as of November 01, 2002 (the first storage release date of the new crop year) were 201,199 MT, a 5.5% decrease from the 213,013 MT in storage the previous year at the same time.
Only the province of Quebec recorded an increase while other major provinces recorded decreases varying from 2% to 27% (see Table 3).
