Much of the country’s growth has come thanks to a rapidly expanding export sector.
Export growth since 1990 has exceeded China’s and Vietnam is now challenging even the most dominant countries in their "Bread and Butter" exports, such as with Brazil and coffee, India and tea, and Thailand and rice.
The truly remarkable aspect of this growth is the trickle down to the general population.
While Vietnam is still one of the Asia’s poorest countries, GDP PPP has tripled since 1990.
