Lastly, product extension or the introduction of new flavors has been used as a tool to attract consumers.
While the leading brands have the most number of variants, the new players are utilizing this approach to gain market share.
Ajinomoto, for instance, recently introduced flavors never before seen in the market like lychee and guava, while Zest-O Corporation's Sunglo has a strawberry flavor.
At the same time, Eight o' Clock has combined-flavored drinks like orange-mango, and orange-pineapple.
Prospects Research firm AC Nielsen reported that the market for powdered juice drinks is still growing although at a slower rate compared to ready-to-drink juices.
According to players, they expect the segment to post continued growth in the next three to five years.
Performance will be driven mainly by strong demand for economy packs while those in bigger packs will continue to post steady growth rates.
The entry of new players, despite the pull-out of URC, indicates a growing market.
Existing players view this as a challenge since more would mean more product options for the consumer.
