Market Players Two local brewers, San Miguel Corporation (SMC) and Asia Brewery Inc (ABI), dominate the Philippine beer market.
SMC controls 90% of the market while ABI and the other imported brands hold the balance of 10%.
Clearly, the good performance of the beer division reflects SMC's strong market position and numerous distribution channels.
The strength of beer sales did not rest on the Philippine market alone.
SMC is present in Vietnam, Thailand, Hong Kong, China, Indonesia and Australia.
For its international beer operations, volume increased by 11% in 2005 generating US$284 million in revenues, up by 8% in 2004.
Moreover, consolidated operating income also went up by 33% to US$12.9 million.
The company also produces foreign beer brands such as James Boag Premium Lager, Anker Bir, Miller Genuine Draft and Lowenbrau.
