More than 84% of the total imports in 2000 were fresh and the rest were dried.
On the average, the country imported 112 tons yearly of fresh cutflowers and 110 tons annually of dried flowers from 1991-2000.
Fresh imports reached 110 tons in 2000, almost 50% lower than the previous year's 212 tons.
