National Statistics Office (NSO) Over the last five years, total imports reached 2,600 tons worth US$4.2 million.
Major sources were the United States, (64% of volume), followed by China (20%), Indonesia (7%), and Canada (6%).
The United States was the leading supplier of peanut butter to the Philippines with volume reaching almost 2,000 tons worth US$3.5 million.
