Production With limited data available, the total production of fruit spreads is difficult to ascertain.
However, one fruit spread manufacturer cited the average production capacity for jams and marmalades is around 60,000 cases a month, with a capacity utilization of about 70%.
Normally, the plant operates six days a week but can easily adjust production schedules if there is a demand hike, especially during holiday season.
While fruit production is located in the rural areas, most processing plants are concentrated in Metro Manila particularly for fruit spreads.
Trade The country imports and exports jams, marmalades and jellies.
Exports.
The bulk of fruit spreads exports were jams and marmalades, accounting for 97% of export value in 2000.
