Bone chip found in US beef A bone chip has been discovered in the first shipment of US beef to land in Korea.
The Ministry of Agriculture and Forestry (MAF) announced that a small piece of bone was discovered in a box of chuck flap tail - the bone was detected through the x-ray process by which every carton is being inspected.
