CIF (Cost, Insurance and Freight):
The landed value of merchandise at the first port of arrival in the importing country.
It is computed by adding "Import Charges" to the "Customs Value" and therefore excludes import duties.
FOB (Free On Board):
The value of exports as they are moved onto the ship at the port of export.
The buyer bears all costs and risks of loss of or damage to the goods from that point.
The FOB term requires the seller to clear the goods for export.
This term is used only for sea or inland waterway transport.
For other modes of transport the FCA (Free Carrier) term should be used.
