Significant market research is required to determine and match local consumer preferences.
For example, a leading brand's plain potato chip has a small amount of sugar in the ingredients.
Popular chip brands include seaweed, shrimp, roasted pork or curry, whereas in Canada, they are Ketchup and Sour Cream and Onion.
