• Imported brands produced in China have greater success.
They are able to compete on price, market awareness and production costs.
• Price, taste and branding are key elements to understanding the Shanghainese consumer.
As any market, consumer preferences vary immensely from the Canadian market.
Effective and adequate market research should be performed to ensure an understanding of the market.
