What's New Manitoba's Peak of the Market wins first Canada Brand Award at SIAL Montreal Montreal - Peak of the Market was "surprised but thrilled" to win the first Canada Brand Award presented March 28 at SIAL Montreal 2007.
"We know there are a lot of great companies across Canada and were really honoured to be recognized in this way," said Larry McIntosh, president and CEO of Peak of the Market.
Peak of the Market is a Manitoba company currently exporting to the United States as well as into Asia, Europe, Latin America and the Caribbean.
The award was presented at the inaugural Canadian Agri-Food Export Gala held during SIAL Montreal, a three-day international food show held every two years.
Over 700 companies from 34 countries participated.
"We are a very proud Canadian company.
We talk about Canada in almost everything we do…on our website, business cards, bags and cartons," McIntosh said.
"Even our new logo says "Proudly Canadian" on it.
We believe this helps us to sell our quality vegetables, not just in Canada, but especially in our export markets."
The Canada Brand Award, sponsored by Agri-Food Export Group Quebec, is awarded to a company that has, among other things: ▪ invested resources to build customer relationships and understand their particular needs, offer solutions and provide continuous improvement; ▪ put processes in place to assure consistent quality and safety attributes in their products; and ▪ demonstrated a commitment to innovation and respect for the environment.
As a result, Canada's reputation is enhanced as a trustworthy and reliable supplier that exceeds customers' expectations.
Peak of the Market receives $5,000 and a promotion plan prepared for Canadian and international markets.
"I truly believe that using the Canada brand has helped our company increase its sales," McIntosh told the gala audience.
"Canada is internationally known for being friendly, having clean, wide-open spaces and high quality food products.
