What's New The Canada Brand supports a winning marketing campaign in Malaysia A Canada Brand member recently won a prestigious marketing award for its product line of Halal foods.
Maple Lodge Farms captured the Halal Journal award for Most Creative Marketing for its Zabiha Halal chicken products at the World Halal Forum gala in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia on May 7, 2007.
More than 1,000 people attended the gala including royalty and the country's prime minister.
A video introducing the award winners included Maple Lodge Farms saying it was proud to offer Canadian products where "Quality is in our Nature."
An ad for the Zabiha product line, located prominently on the first inside page of the magazine, also included a tasteful design using the Canada Brand graphics and tag-line.
"Maple Lodge Farms' foray into branded Halal products is an important step in capturing a portion of the global Halal food trade, estimated at $560 billion US annually," said Bruce Howard, Regional Agri-Food Trade Commissioner with the Canadian High Commission in Singapore.
"Halal food for the world's 1.6 billion Muslims must meet strict food safety and religious requirements and Maple Lodge Farms has proven itself up to this challenge.
This award furthers the message that Canada is a supplier of superior Halal products."
Anthony Tavares, CEO of Maple Lodge Farms underlined the importance of the research undertaken by his company in re-branding and expanding its Halal product line in 2004.
"We undertook extensive market research and studied demographics to better understand the needs of our Muslim customers," he said.
Maple Lodge Farms worked with retailers to make their expanded line of Halal products more widely available in mainstream grocery stores.
Consumer focus group testing helped select the striking design that won the Halal Journal award, and the Canada Brand graphics and tag-line are included in the company's international marketing material.
"We are excited by the opportunities in international markets," stated Mr. Tavares.
"Canada has a reputation for quality and we expect that using the Canada Brand will emphasize the quality of our products."
The brand will also be used in other advertising media, including on delivery vehicles in Dubai, United Arab Emirates, where Maple Lodge Farms' Zabiha products have recently appeared on store shelves.
