What is the Canada brand?
What's in it for me?
The Brand Canada initiative, with supporting tools, can help you grow your markets and sell more products.
What's more, Canada's branding strategy was designed to be flexible and can be adapted to various markets and sectors.
Ultimately, branding Canada offers us an opportunity to grow our markets and sell more products.
In turn, as your products are successful in the market place, you add value to the Canada brand.
What's in it for the sector?
Many advantages, including a stronger international presence and opportunities for growth.
To put it in perspective, last year, Canada exported over $30 billion (Cdn) worth of food and agriculture around the world.
Almost half of Canadian domestic food and agricultural production is exported either directly as primary products or indirectly as part of processed products.
Yet in any one market, Canada's presence is small!
Countries with lower production costs and longer growing seasons are bringing more bulk commodities to market at lower prices – and making it hard for Canada to compete on price in traditional areas of strength.
But while the number of suppliers on world markets is increasing, so too, are the number of potential customers.
Those customers are demanding food that is safe and produced in an environmentally responsible way.
Customers, faced with an abundance of competing product information often make decisions based on general impressions.
So we took that positive image to develop a comprehensive brand to help Canadian exporters and marketers set Canadian products apart from the competition.
Branding Canada in international markets has a key role to play in the future of Canada's food and agriculture sector.
As soon as anyone sees or hears of a Canadian food or agricultural product, we want them to instinctively decide that the product will meet or exceed their expectations.
▪ What's in it for the sector? ▪ What's in it for me? ▪ The Canada brand promise ▪ Market research results ▪ Canada brand core attributes password protected Why?
Because it's from Canada.
The Canada brand is our image and reputation.
It's what customers can expect to experience, every time they deal with us.
We want them to think that: ▪ our products are excellent ▪ as a multi-cultural country we focus on customers and respond to the needs of our international clients ▪ as an industry, we are committed to continuous improvements Successful organizations that have developed a strong brand know who they are and why they are relevant to their customers.
How they look, what they do, the way they sound and how they promote themselves are all consistent with the way they want to be perceived in the market place.
And, what they stand for is captured in a brand promise with core attributes that they want to be known for.
We invite you to incorporate and adapt the Canada brand promise to your particular business.
Branding Canada's food and agriculture sector is a commitment by industry and government to excellence and quality.
Once we make that commitment and live up to it, the Canada brand will flourish and everyone will benefit.
