On the other hand, some hogs on offer had not attained the minimum finishing weight and were thus rejected by traders.
Overall, market supplies have remained low.
Due to the significant price difference between live production hogs and pork consumption, traders were able to make a good profit.
Near-term prices in the hog production regions may rise more strongly on positive demand, thus narrowing the price gap.
In the last week of December, Guangdong's hog prices were higher than those in Hunan by more than RMB1.00/kg. In Shanghai, prices were RMB1.20-1.50/kg more than those in Jiangsu, Zhejiang and Henan provinces.
In addition, some pigs continued to be affected by diseases which conventional treatment had failed to work.
