Smolt Rearing.
Chile has a substantial advantage in that most of their smolts are lake-reared, a very cheap rearing method (although access to lake rearing will be curtailed in the future).
BC has only a few lake rearing locations, New Brunswick has none.
Chile and Norway both have access to premium stocks from sophisticated breeding programs.
Feed.
Norway has been slow to replace fish meal and oil components by a vegetable component, but gets good Feed Conversion Ratios (FCRs).
Canada has ready access to non-marine ingredients.
Chile is close to production facilities in fish meal and oil.
Wage Rates.
Wage rates in Canada are substantially higher than in Chile but lower than in Norway.
