Pink and chum salmon, always abundant from Alaskan, Japanese, or Russian fisheries if not from BC, offer wild salmon alternatives at budget prices.
To be marketed as a premium wild salmon and command premium prices, however, sockeye salmon must meet lofty customer expectations.
Other "premium" attributes associated with top-quality sockeye salmon are firm flesh texture, bright skin colour, and high oil/fat content.
