Beans/Lentils Pulses are the dry seeds of legumes, including peas, beans, lentils, and chick peas.
Canada grows high-quality pulses at relatively low costs.
Our cool climate provides pulse crops with natural protection against insects and disease.
In addition, Canada has a well-established infrastructure to store and move grain and pulses from the producing regions to the port terminals.
