Traditional-style Canadian Pea Soup
1 kg dried peas (split yellow peas) 300 g salt pork 50 g lard 100 g carrots, diced 100 g celery, diced – 40 – 100 g onion, diced 1 bunch parsley, coarsely chopped 1 bouquet garni 1 bay leaf salt and pepper
Method Soak the peas in cold water for 12 hours to soften.
Place the salt pork in a saucepan and add enough cold water to cover.
Bring to boil.
Drain off liquid.
Dice the cooked pork and sauté briefly in lard.
Add the softened peas, vegetables, bouquet garni, parsley, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
