Saskatoon Berries Saskatoons have been a widely used native Prairie fruit crop.
Commercial Saskatoon berry production is a relatively new development.
Although the first Saskatoon orchard in Manitoba was planted less than 15 years ago, current planted acreage makes the Saskatoon berry the second largest commercial fruit crop in Manitoba today, second only to strawberries.
Primary market studies indicate the potential to produce, process and export Saskatoon berry products is worldwide.
Consumers are attracted to the unique subtle flavour of a "wild" fruit product made from Saskatoon berries.
