Beer Beer was first brewed in Canada three centuries ago by our early settlers and traders.
After Jean Talon built Canada’s first commercial brewery in 1668 in the City of Québec, beer making was a cottage industry for the next century.
The first brewery in Montréal was established in 1786.
This event marked the beginning of the industry’s development period as small, independent breweries began to open across the country.
By the 1870s, brewing was a strong, modern industry with brewers located across the country, from the Maritimes to British Columbia.
